## v5.0.0

### Breaking changes

- `ArdiumInputComponent` (`<ard-input>`) is now renamed to `ArdiumAutocompleteInputComponent` (`<ard-autocomplete-input>`)
- `ArdiumSimpleInputComponent` (`<ard-simple-input>`) is now renamed to `ArdiumInputComponent` (`<ard-input>`)
- All boolean-coerced inputs now use `@ardium-ui/devkit`'s `BooleanLike` type instead of `any`
- Select, Checkbox List, and Segment now do not use any signals in their template contexts. All context fields are now primitive
- Tabber and Tab now use a single function for providing their default values (`provideTabberDefaults`)
- Slider and Range Slider label objects are now defined as `{ label: string, value: number }[]` (was: `{ label: string, for: number }[]`)
- Calendar & Date Input now always use UTC dates in templates and template contexts
- Range Slider now emits its value as `{ from: number, to: number }` (was: `{ low: number, high: number }`)
- Button, FAB, and Icon Button now place their content directly inside the `<button>` element.
  - Removed `.ard-focus-overlay`. It was used to add a colored overlay over the background, now `::before` is used for that purpose
  - Removed `.ard-button-content`. It was used to add flexbox to the content, now the button itself does that
  - Removed `[icon]` and `[iconAlign]` inputs from Button. Use `<ard-icon>` instead.
- `ard-chip`, `ard-deletable-chip`, `ard-selectable-chip`'s `'filled'` variant is now named `'filled-strong'`. The `'filled'` variant still exists, but has new styling.
- `OneAxisAlignment.Middle` (`'middle'`) is now renamed to `OneAxisAlignment.Center` (`'center'`) in all use cases. This change affects:
  - `ard-card-action-buttons` (`[align]`)
  - `ard-chip`, `ard-selectable-chip`, `ard-deletable-chip` (`[contentAlignment]`)
  - `ard-form-field`, `ard-horizontal-form-field` (`[defaultHintAlign]`)
  - `ard-input`, `ard-autocomplete-input`, `ard-number-input` (`[alignText]`)
  - `ard-segment` (`[align]`)
  - `ard-tabber` (`[tabAlignment]`)

### Additions & Changes

- **New Components**
  - Date Range Input & Range Calendar
    - For selecting ranges of two dates, with all features of normal calendar
  - Multipage Date Range Input
    - Specialized date range input that shows multiple calendar pages (multiple months) at once. It doesn't let the user select years and months directly, just the dates.
  - Grid & Stack
    - Grid is for positioning elements horizontally in a column-based layout
    - Stack is a shortcut for positioning elements using flexbox
- Button
  - Added button directive that can be used on a `<button>` or an `<a>` element to add all button functionality
  - Button component now uses the directive internally
- Checkbox List
  - Allow to customize the checkboxes and labels using respective template directives
- Checkbox, Selectable Chip, Slide Toggle, Star Button
  - Added `[reverseSelected]` input - if set to true, the component will appear selected when the actual value is `false`. This is a purely visual change and does not affect the actual value.
- Date Input & Calendar
  - Added `[UTC]` input - outputed values are in UTC format. Defaults for UTC input are supported as well
  - Added `[startView]` input - can be configured to set which calendar view is shown when opening the date input
  - Created `isDateRange` and `isYearRange` type guard functions
- Dialog & Modal
  - A class can now be added to the modal overlay element
  - Dialog confirm button now supports setting the `[pointerEventsWhenDisabled]` input
- Divider
  - Now supports adding content
  - Now also available as a directive, alongside the component
  - Added `[flexItem]` input which fixes the divider styling when used inside flexbox containers
  - Added `[variant]` input which changes the shape of the divider (supported: `"full"` which spans the whole container, and `"middle"` which adds some margin on the sides)
  - Added `[textAlign]` input which aligns the content to either the start, the center, or the end of the divider
  - Divider border style can now be set via a CSS variable
- Form Field
  - Errors now support being aligned to the left and right side, not only to the left
  - Added `[defaultHintAlign]` input - configures which is the default side that hints and errors will align to
  - Added `ard-hint-error` component and directive - they behave like both the hint and the error, which means they appear even when no other errors are specified, but they still stay and change color to red when other errors are defined
  - Added `ard-auto-error` component, which automatically generates an error message based on the `FormControl`'s state
  - Labels are now styled properly when the field has an error
  - Now also supports the Rating Input component as the control
- Input
  - Added `[autoTrim]` input - when set to true, the input value will be trimmed on blur
- Number Input
  - Now supports `ard-prefix-tmp` and `ard-suffix-tmp` customization templates
  - Added `[maxDecimalPlaces]` input for deciding how many decimal places may be passed in. All further digits are trimmed (rounded down)
  - Added `[fixedDecimalPlaces]` input - when set to true, there will be a fixed number of decimal places displayed (fixes the places on blur)
  - Added `[decimalSeparator]` input that allows to customize the decimal separator. Any single character string can be used. Using the dot still works, but the dot is converted to the specified separator
  - Added `[minMaxBehavior]` input that allows to set when is the number input value adjusted to the min/max value (available options: `'adjust-on-blur'` (default), `'adjust-on-input'`, `'noop'`)
- Select
  - Added `[dropdownPanelWidth]`, `[dropdownPanelHeight]`, `[dropdownPanelMinWidth]`, `[dropdownPanelMinHeight]`, `[dropdownPanelMaxWidth]`, and `[dropdownPanelMaxHeight]` inputs
  - Added `[addCustomOptionText]` input - allows to change what the "Add custom option" text is without having to change the template
  - Allow to customize the dropdown arrow using a template directive
  - Adding a custom option is now available at all times, unless an exact match is found
  - Dropdown is no longer opened when pressing Enter
  - Added `totalItemsCount` and `itemsSelectedCount` to the value template context
- Slide Toggle
  - Added CSS styles for `"contained"` appearance, as the typescript portion was working, but the styles were missing
- Slider & Range Slider
  - An error is now thrown when trying to set `[min]` to a value greater than `[max]`
  - Added `[selectionBehavior]` input to Range Slider - allows to change how the handles can move in relation to each other
    - Value `"allow"` permits the handles to pass each other, while keeping the value in order (default).
    - Value `"block"` doesn't let the handles move past each other
    - Value `"push"` doesn't let the handles move past each other, but the other handle is moved alongside the current handle if necessary
  - Added `[minimumDistance]` input to Range Slider - allows to change how much distance should be between the handles in `"block"` and `"push"` mode
  - The `[labels]` input now allows to coerce its value from a string, allowing for defining the labels as `"0,20,40,60,80,100"` instead of `[0, 20, 40, 60, 80, 100]`
  - Sliders now allow to control the handles with Up & Down Arrows, PageUp, PageDown, Home, and End keyboard keys
- Tabber
  - Allow to change the label template for individual tabs by passing in a `TemplateRef` into the `[label]` input, or for all tabs by using a custom template directive
  - Added `[(selectedTabId)]` two-way binding

### Styling Changes

**All components now support CSS customization using CSS variables.** All variables can be freely modified.

**All components now use CSS layers.** Component-level styles use the `ard-cmp` layer, while theme-level files use the `ard-theme` layer. By default, the layer order is undefined - it can be defined explicitly if needed. If not defined, standard CSS rules apply.

All components now use the `--ard-font-family` css variable to define their font family.

Other notable changes include:

- Checkbox List
  - Added some padding above the first element

### Bug Fixes

- Added `display: block` to almost all components (some use `inline-block` or similar). Only a few components now remain as `inline` because they are usually used within text.
- Calendar year template context variable shows the previous year due to timezone issues
- Calendar heading buttons change when the button defaults are provided
- Some Calendar did not support providing default values
- Input, Autocomplete Input, and Hex Input didn't use the native HTML `maxlength` attribute
- Form Field hints & errors don't to the next line when too long
- Select dropdown panel goes off the screen when select is positioned very close to the right side of the screen
- Input, Autocomplete Input, Date Input, Hex Input, Password Input, and Select don't add the `readonly` attribute to their template
- Input, Autocomplete Input, Date Input, Hex Input, Password Input, and Select don't put the caret at the beginning when clicking to the left of the text
- Input, Autocomplete Input, Date Input, Hex Input, Password Input, and Select flash the border on initial page load
- Select causes a freeze when using `[formControl]` to set value from inside an effect
- Select value overflows the field when too long
- Select has the clear button even when it is read-only
- Select is susceptible to race conditions if the value and the items both load asynchronously
- Select shows a warning that an option was not found if both the value and the options are changed at the same time
- Select emits touched event too early when an option is being selected, causing a split-second flash of error state
- Fixed several signal usages being passed in directly instead of by its value, causing it to always be treated as `true`
- Modals & Dialogs can overflow the viewport when they have too much content
- Dialog emits the close event twice
- Radios' circles shrink and become egg-like when they don't fit
- File Input & File Drop Area have a leftover console.log statement
- Number Input doesn't take into account the default values provided using its provider function
- Number Input doesn't emit its value for Reactive Forms
- Number Input has zero as its default value, while it should be null
- Number Input removes leading zeros and trailing decimal separators on every keystroke (should remove only on blur)
- Checkbox List items do not have the `ard-item-selected` class when selected
- Checkbox List doesn't emit touched event when using the mouse to select values
- Tabber doesn't set the intial tab correctly
- Slider and Range Slider do not fix their value automatically when min, max, or step are changed
- Slider and Range Slider do not have the `grab` cursor when hovering over the handle, and the `grabbing` cursor when moving the handle
- Slider and Range Slider tooltip value wraps into the second line even though it shouldn't
- Range Slider sets its initial value to a range from `-Infinity` to `+Infinity` instead of from `min` to `max`
- Digit Input and Radio Group had `allowSignalWrites` set to true, which caused warnings to be displayed in the console
- Rating Display only uses one color for all stars, even the unselected ones, while they should be uncolored
- Rating Input doesn't fire ControlValueAccessor touched events
- Rating Input fires ControlValueAccessor change events with a delay
- Tabber's tabs accept the disabled attribute, but do not disable the actual tab buttons
